WEBVTT

00:03.037 --> 00:04.870
(grand orchestral fanfare
            playing)

00:39.840 --> 00:42.875
(organ playing George Michael's
        "Heal the Pain")

00:56.157 --> 01:00.559
¶ Ooh ¶

01:00.561 --> 01:05.397
¶ Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh ¶

01:05.399 --> 01:09.735
¶ Ooh ¶

01:09.737 --> 01:12.404
¶ Ooh-ooh-ooh ¶

01:12.406 --> 01:15.274
¶ Let me tell you a secret ¶

01:15.276 --> 01:18.777
¶ Put it in your heart
         and keep it ¶

01:18.779 --> 01:22.114
¶ Something that
      I want you to know ¶

01:22.116 --> 01:24.516
¶ Do something for me ¶

01:24.518 --> 01:27.553
¶ Listen to my simple story ¶

01:27.555 --> 01:31.356
¶ And maybe we'll have
      something to show ¶

01:31.358 --> 01:34.626
¶ You tell me you're cold
        on the inside ¶

01:34.628 --> 01:36.962
¶ How can the outside world ¶

01:36.964 --> 01:41.200
¶ Be a place that your heart
         can embrace? ¶

01:41.202 --> 01:45.437
¶ Be good to yourself
      'cause nobody else ¶

01:45.439 --> 01:49.274
¶ Has the power
      to make you happy ¶

01:49.276 --> 01:51.910
¶ How can I help you? ¶

01:51.912 --> 01:53.879
¶ Please let me try to ¶

01:53.881 --> 01:55.881
¶ I can heal the pain ¶

01:55.883 --> 01:58.450
-¶ That you're feeling inside ¶
       -(clicking teeth)

01:58.452 --> 02:00.752
¶ Whenever you want me ¶

02:00.754 --> 02:05.290
¶ Know that I will be
     waiting for the day ¶

02:05.292 --> 02:08.259
¶ That you say you'll be mine ¶

02:08.262 --> 02:09.794
¶ Do do do ¶

02:09.797 --> 02:12.297
¶ Do do do do ¶

02:12.299 --> 02:17.102
¶ Do do do do,
      do do do do do... ¶

02:17.104 --> 02:21.740
¶ Do do do do, do do do do ¶

02:21.742 --> 02:24.076
(humming)

02:24.078 --> 02:26.145
You look like you need another.

02:26.147 --> 02:27.980
What are you, psychic?

02:27.982 --> 02:29.081
Look deep into my eyes.

02:29.083 --> 02:31.016
(chuckles)

02:31.018 --> 02:33.085
Yeah.
  You're feeling very thirsty.

02:33.087 --> 02:35.087
Oh, you are very good.

02:35.089 --> 02:37.089
-And... -("Heal the Pain"
   by George Michael playing)

02:37.091 --> 02:38.924
Oh, yeah,
  this is your favorite song.

02:38.926 --> 02:40.259
That was so psychic.

02:40.261 --> 02:42.961
No, that was you playing it
      four times in a row.

02:42.963 --> 02:44.530
Well, love me,
      love George Michael.

02:44.532 --> 02:46.098
We're kindred spirits.

02:46.100 --> 02:48.333
-How so?
   -Well, we're both singers.

02:48.335 --> 02:49.768
Uh, we're both
     famously misunderstood

02:49.770 --> 02:51.203
and underappreciated
          in our time.

02:51.205 --> 02:53.105
But all that's gonna change,

02:53.107 --> 02:55.274
'cause tomorrow I've got a
 big audition for the West End.

02:55.276 --> 02:58.177
And you, uh,
     came into town for it?

02:58.179 --> 03:00.679
No, I, uh, moved out
     on my flatmate today.

03:00.681 --> 03:02.114
So, what,
  you're gonna move back home?

03:02.116 --> 03:05.284
-Oh, kill me now.
     -Uh-oh. Family issues.

03:05.286 --> 03:07.052
Yeah. Let me count the ways.

03:07.054 --> 03:09.121
Um, anger, shame, resentment,

03:09.123 --> 03:10.455
embarrassment--
    and that's just my mum.

03:10.457 --> 03:12.124
Do you want to hear
        about my sister?

03:12.126 --> 03:13.125
-No. Okay.
          -(laughing)

03:13.127 --> 03:14.660
So, what's your plan?

03:14.662 --> 03:16.028
I'll figure it out, you know.

03:16.030 --> 03:17.663
It'll be fine.
    Something will turn up.

03:17.665 --> 03:19.298
Or someone.

03:22.570 --> 03:25.837
Morning, gorgeous.

03:25.839 --> 03:29.208
This bed, it's like sleeping
     on a pile of kittens.

03:30.344 --> 03:32.844
If that thought's comfortable

03:32.846 --> 03:34.913
-and not completely horrifying.
          -(chuckles)

03:34.915 --> 03:36.682
I'm gonna dash down the street.

03:36.684 --> 03:38.517
I need some gingerroot,
          fresh beets

03:38.519 --> 03:40.152
for my famous
     breakfast power juice.

03:40.154 --> 03:41.753
-Cool.
            -And...

03:41.755 --> 03:44.723
-a cappuccino while you wait.
             -Wow.

03:44.725 --> 03:46.892
And lashings of hot water
     if you fancy a shower.

03:46.894 --> 03:50.028
-Bliss.
      -I'll be right back.

03:50.030 --> 03:51.930
(sighs, chuckles)

03:51.932 --> 03:54.032
-(door opens)
       -WOMAN: Surprise!

03:54.034 --> 03:56.335
Guess who got back from
  the conference a day early.

03:56.337 --> 03:57.769
God, I've missed you.

03:57.771 --> 03:59.571
(both scream)

03:59.573 --> 04:00.672
God, who are you?!

04:00.674 --> 04:02.407
I'm the... plumber.

04:02.409 --> 04:03.442
-The plumber?
      -Look... (stammers)

04:03.444 --> 04:04.676
This isn't what it looks like.
           I just...

04:04.678 --> 04:06.245
I just... I needed a bed
    for the night, and he...

04:06.247 --> 04:09.014
-Ed. -Ed. Ed was just
       so understanding.

04:09.016 --> 04:10.782
And I-I just... I just... I've
 got lots of issues, all right?

04:10.784 --> 04:12.517
Accommodation, firstly, 'cause
I've sort of run out of options

04:12.519 --> 04:14.253
because I've really messed up
    for a number of reasons.

04:14.255 --> 04:15.420
-And he...
              -Ed.

04:15.422 --> 04:17.555
Ed just seemed to get that.

04:17.558 --> 04:18.724
Did you shag him?

04:18.726 --> 04:21.026
("Last Christmas"
       by Wham! playing)

04:21.028 --> 04:22.527
(grunts, shouts)

04:22.529 --> 04:25.030
Look, you took my bag!

04:25.032 --> 04:26.198
(stammers, grunts)

04:26.200 --> 04:28.433
Ow!

04:28.435 --> 04:30.402
(scoffs)

04:30.404 --> 04:32.371
Why is my life so shit?!

04:32.373 --> 04:34.139
¶ Last Christmas ¶

04:34.141 --> 04:36.208
¶ I gave you my heart ¶

04:36.210 --> 04:38.710
¶ But the very next day ¶

04:38.712 --> 04:41.980
¶ You gave it away ¶

04:41.982 --> 04:44.783
¶ This year,
    to save me from tears ¶

04:44.785 --> 04:50.289
¶ I'll give it
      to someone special ¶

04:50.291 --> 04:54.393
¶ Last Christmas,
     I gave you my heart ¶

04:54.395 --> 04:57.462
¶ But the very next day,
       you gave it away ¶

04:57.464 --> 04:59.131
-(groans)
     -¶ You gave it away ¶

04:59.133 --> 05:03.502
¶ This year,
    to save me from tears ¶

05:03.504 --> 05:06.471
¶ I'll give it
      to someone special ¶

05:06.473 --> 05:08.307
¶ Special ¶

05:25.025 --> 05:26.458
(kazoo buzzing)

05:26.460 --> 05:27.793
¶ Once bitten... ¶

05:27.795 --> 05:30.095
It's not funny, Klaus.

05:30.097 --> 05:32.431
It's incredible
       how unfunny it is.

05:32.433 --> 05:35.267
¶ But you still catch my eye ¶

05:35.269 --> 05:37.269
¶ Tell me, baby ¶

05:37.271 --> 05:39.805
¶ Do you recognize me? ¶

05:39.807 --> 05:41.973
-(bell jingles)
  -¶ Well, it's been a year ¶

05:41.975 --> 05:44.643
¶ It doesn't surprise me ¶

05:44.645 --> 05:46.211
¶ Merry Christmas ¶

05:46.213 --> 05:49.281
¶ I wrapped it up
     and sent it with... ¶

05:49.283 --> 05:51.049
-(bell jingles)
            -(sighs)

05:54.388 --> 05:56.521
(power whirring)

05:56.523 --> 05:59.291
("Last Christmas"
   by Little Voices playing)

05:59.293 --> 06:00.525
(sighs):
            Christ.

06:00.527 --> 06:01.860
CHILDREN'S CHOIR:
     ¶ Last Christmas... ¶

06:01.862 --> 06:05.364
(groans)
       I'm sorry, George.

06:05.366 --> 06:06.631
(sighs)

06:06.633 --> 06:08.300
(whispers):
         Happy. Happy.

06:08.302 --> 06:09.868
Happy. Happy.

06:09.870 --> 06:13.472
¶ This year,
    to save me from tears ¶

06:13.474 --> 06:18.043
¶ I'll give it
    to someone special... ¶

06:21.315 --> 06:22.914
Hey, you're early.

06:22.916 --> 06:26.084
You are never early.
      What are you up to?

06:26.086 --> 06:27.319
Accommodation issues.

06:27.321 --> 06:29.721
Hmm. So the usual.
   What did you do this time?

06:29.723 --> 06:32.391
-Fry someone's fish?
  -No, no, that was last week.

06:32.393 --> 06:36.194
-(blow dryer whirring) -¶ Hey,
 you're just too funky for me ¶

06:36.196 --> 06:37.562
-(electrical crackling)
   -¶ I gotta get inside... ¶

06:37.564 --> 06:38.764
(music stops)

06:40.734 --> 06:43.502
You are going to run out
     of friends with sofas.

06:43.504 --> 06:44.870
You have been sick.

06:44.872 --> 06:46.405
You need to take care
      of yourself better.

06:46.407 --> 06:48.573
-Santa, I didn't know
   you cared. -I don't care.

06:48.575 --> 06:50.442
I just don't want you to drop
dead in front of the customers.

06:50.444 --> 06:53.345
I don't have enough tinsel
     to cover your corpse.

06:53.347 --> 06:55.013
Get to work, elf.

06:57.684 --> 06:59.684
(groans quietly)

07:00.954 --> 07:02.287
I don't know.

07:02.289 --> 07:03.922
You're gonna have to
        help me decide.

07:03.924 --> 07:06.091
-They're both so darling.
       -I tell you what.

07:06.093 --> 07:08.794
Let's pretend Mary had twins,
     and you can get both.

07:08.796 --> 07:10.095
(both laugh)

07:10.097 --> 07:11.596
You must just love your job.

07:11.598 --> 07:14.366
-Love it.
  -It's like being in a dream.

07:14.368 --> 07:17.402
All the joys and the love
          of Christmas

07:17.404 --> 07:20.205
-every single day of the year.
          -(chuckles)

07:20.207 --> 07:21.807
Now, which baby
       is it going to be?

07:21.809 --> 07:24.409
He's gorgeous, but this one...

07:24.411 --> 07:26.144
he looks like he's having
         a lot of fun.

07:26.146 --> 07:28.246
-Oh, yeah, and a lot more
     to come. -(both laugh)

07:28.248 --> 07:30.816
-But this one, look at him.
         -Come on. Hey.

07:30.818 --> 07:32.117
-He's more like my idea of...
         -Jesus Christ.

07:32.119 --> 07:33.652
-You think so, too?
           -Katarina.

07:33.654 --> 07:35.387
Um, excuse me
  for just one moment. Santa!

07:35.389 --> 07:36.388
I need a word.

07:36.390 --> 07:37.789
I'm at work.
    You could've called me.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.224
You're not answering
          your phone.

07:39.226 --> 07:40.559
Remember?
   Look, I've come from work.

07:40.561 --> 07:42.761
I need to get back,
     so come get out here.

07:42.763 --> 07:44.563
That's my analyst.
           So sorry.

07:44.565 --> 07:46.398
Santa, can you get
       down here, please?

07:46.400 --> 07:49.267
Please? Thank you.

07:49.269 --> 07:51.470
Santa?

07:51.472 --> 07:53.505
Are you there?

07:54.508 --> 07:56.942
Mum needs you to ring her.

07:56.944 --> 07:58.410
All right, every time
        she contacts you

07:58.412 --> 08:00.412
and gets no response,
        she contacts me.

08:00.414 --> 08:02.280
Yesterday, 17 times.

08:02.282 --> 08:04.483
-Just do it. -Oh, don't just
 stand there issuing commands.

08:04.485 --> 08:06.151
I am an adult.

08:06.153 --> 08:08.720
You are the furthest thing
   from an adult that I know.

08:09.756 --> 08:11.456
I need time to myself.

08:11.458 --> 08:14.693
I'm asking you to do
   a single thing, Katarina.

08:14.695 --> 08:15.694
It's "Kate."

08:15.696 --> 08:17.329
Whatever. Just ring her.
          Contact her.

08:17.331 --> 08:18.530
Give me one good reason.

08:18.532 --> 08:20.532
You've missed five
     doctor's appointments.

08:20.534 --> 08:21.867
You've got one planned
 for tomorrow, which apparently

08:21.869 --> 08:23.301
you know about.
     You have to be there.

08:23.303 --> 08:25.670
She's also planning a dinner
   to celebrate my promotion.

08:25.672 --> 08:29.140
And you not ringing her
is seriously affecting my life.

08:29.142 --> 08:32.043
Will you be inviting Alba
         to the dinner?

08:33.046 --> 08:35.113
Just ring your mother.

08:35.115 --> 08:37.048
Christ.

08:37.049 --> 08:38.850
(sighs)

08:38.852 --> 08:40.184
Yeah, Jenna, it's me.
        Listen, darling,

08:40.187 --> 08:41.520
I'm sorry
     to leave this message.

08:41.522 --> 08:43.455
I just really need
      a bed for the night.

08:43.457 --> 08:45.023
Even possibly a few nights.

08:45.025 --> 08:46.625
-You're my bestie. Please.
       I know. -(grunts)

08:46.627 --> 08:48.126
-Just...
           -Hey, elf!

08:48.128 --> 08:49.828
This is my elf.

08:49.830 --> 08:51.363
Santa has elves, you know.

08:51.365 --> 08:53.064
Little helpers.

08:53.066 --> 08:54.900
I have nicknamed her
         "Lazy the Elf"

08:54.902 --> 08:56.501
because she appears
         never to work.

08:56.503 --> 08:58.403
-That's me. Mm.
   -She could also be called

08:58.405 --> 09:00.505
-"Crushing Disappointment
     the Elf." -(laughter)

09:00.507 --> 09:02.574
-I-I'm just... (clears throat)
  -"Waste of Payroll the Elf,"

09:02.576 --> 09:04.209
"Bleeding Me Dry the Elf,"

09:04.211 --> 09:06.378
"Why on Earth Is She
      Even Here the Elf."

09:06.380 --> 09:07.546
(Santa speaking Mandarin)

09:07.548 --> 09:08.914
(grunts)

09:10.183 --> 09:12.551
¶ ¶

09:35.409 --> 09:38.276
(bird chirping)

09:40.247 --> 09:42.380
-What?
        -(gasps) Jesus.

09:42.382 --> 09:44.349
-Where'd you come from?
-Well, what are you looking at?

09:44.351 --> 09:45.884
Look, look.

09:45.886 --> 09:47.953
There. You see it?

09:47.955 --> 09:50.689
-KATE: Oh. -Just above
   the lip of the roof there.

09:50.691 --> 09:53.024
It's quite unusual to see
   a bird like that in town.

09:53.026 --> 09:54.292
-Blimey.
       -(bird screeches)

09:54.294 --> 09:56.595
(groans) Damn it.

09:56.597 --> 09:58.630
Here. Uh, I think
   it just pooed in your eye.

09:58.632 --> 10:00.065
Yeah, I think so.

10:00.067 --> 10:01.700
-SANTA: Goodbye, my people.
       -KATE: Sorry. Ow.

10:01.702 --> 10:03.301
-(Santa speaks Mandarin)
              -Ow.

10:03.303 --> 10:04.402
-Where have you been?
           -(groans)

10:04.404 --> 10:05.403
A shitting bird
      just shat in my eye.

10:05.405 --> 10:06.738
-Oh. Is there a bird in here?
              -No.

10:06.740 --> 10:09.474
Some bloke was outside the shop
     playing silly buggers.

10:09.476 --> 10:11.209
Well, maybe you can focus
         your attention

10:11.211 --> 10:13.211
-on the silly buggers inside
   the shop. -(phone ringing)

10:13.213 --> 10:15.213
I know. Oh! My phone.
         Sorry. Sorry.

10:15.215 --> 10:16.581
I'm sorry, Santa.

10:16.583 --> 10:17.949
Yeah, Jenna!

10:17.951 --> 10:20.385
Yes! Thank you so much.
       Thank you so much.

10:20.387 --> 10:21.953
Thank you so...
 I'll be with you around 8:00.

10:21.955 --> 10:23.555
-Okay. You are number one.
    -Get off the phone now!

10:23.557 --> 10:24.556
Okay, I got to go. Bye.

10:24.558 --> 10:26.291
Yeah, I'm just gonna get
      the shit out my eye.

10:26.293 --> 10:27.759
-I'll be right...
       -Time to sparkle!

10:27.761 --> 10:29.728
¶ Just hear those
    sleigh bells jingling ¶

10:29.730 --> 10:31.563
¶ Ring-ting-tingling, too... ¶

10:31.565 --> 10:34.332
There you are, sir. Enjoy your
 festive hybrid Hanukkah bush.

10:34.334 --> 10:35.467
Merry Christmas to you.
           Thank you.

10:35.469 --> 10:37.135
Thank you. Take care.

10:37.137 --> 10:39.170
(ringtone playing):
¶ She drives me crazy, she... ¶

10:39.172 --> 10:40.572
SANTA:
       Your mother again?

10:40.574 --> 10:42.674
-I curse the day I was born.
           -Me, too.

10:42.676 --> 10:44.609
Ha! Funny, no. I installed
    everything on her phone

10:44.611 --> 10:45.644
from Snapchat to Instagram.

10:45.646 --> 10:47.078
All it means is that

10:47.080 --> 10:48.747
I can disappoint her
    in more ways than ever.

10:48.749 --> 10:50.115
Mothers are hell.

10:50.117 --> 10:51.583
Oh, yeah.

10:51.585 --> 10:52.684
KATE:
              Mm.

10:52.686 --> 10:54.619
Hello.

10:54.621 --> 10:56.855
-Leave him to me.
              -Oh!

10:56.857 --> 10:59.324
You'll just flirt with him, and
 he'll forget to buy anything.

11:00.761 --> 11:01.960
-Hi.
      -How can I help you?

11:01.962 --> 11:04.496
Wouldn't mind finding him
        in my stocking.

11:07.167 --> 11:09.267
-Hi.
        -(yells) Hi. Hi.

11:09.269 --> 11:11.102
I came in to check on your eye.

11:11.104 --> 11:12.270
It's fine.

11:12.272 --> 11:14.005
-It's good luck, you know.
           -What is?

11:14.007 --> 11:15.473
Getting pooed on by a bird.

11:15.475 --> 11:17.475
-Bollocks is it.
        -No, seriously.

11:17.477 --> 11:20.211
So I thought I'd see
         if you fancied

11:20.213 --> 11:22.313
-a little stroll with me.
      -Oh, that's my luck?

11:22.315 --> 11:24.449
-Going for a stroll with you?
           -Might be.

11:24.451 --> 11:26.518
Look, did you find me
           on Swiper?

11:26.520 --> 11:27.719
-Swiper?
             -Yeah.

11:27.721 --> 11:29.821
The modern dating application
    you might have heard of.

11:29.823 --> 11:31.456
Oh. So not.

11:31.458 --> 11:32.857
Look, to be honest,
   you're not really my type.

11:32.859 --> 11:34.492
To be honest,
    you're not really mine.

11:34.494 --> 11:36.127
(opens drawer)

11:36.129 --> 11:38.463
Well, maybe we should
      just leave it, then.

11:38.465 --> 11:40.565
I do like a challenge, though.

11:40.567 --> 11:42.834
-You considered BASE jumping?
        -(closes drawer)

11:42.836 --> 11:44.803
-Japanese blowfish?
          -No, I have,

11:44.805 --> 11:46.838
but right now I'm considering
   a little stroll with you.

11:46.840 --> 11:48.840
Well, consider away,
       because it's a no.

11:48.842 --> 11:50.742
Is there anything
   that I could improve upon

11:50.744 --> 11:52.711
to, say, persuade you?

11:52.713 --> 11:54.412
-No.
   -Any reason in particular?

11:54.414 --> 11:56.314
Because you're weird, this is
  weird, and I don't know you.

11:56.316 --> 11:57.916
So, please, could you
 just leave, okay? Just get...

11:57.918 --> 11:59.484
-Shoo. Just go. Just go.
    -Hold on. This is weird?

11:59.486 --> 12:00.652
Let's just...
      Yeah, you're weird.

12:00.654 --> 12:02.187
-You're strange. I don't
really... -Weirder than Grabber

12:02.189 --> 12:03.421
-or Swiper or whatever
      it's called? -Yeah.

12:04.558 --> 12:06.424
(sighs) Oh, just...

12:06.426 --> 12:08.093
Weirder than total strangers

12:08.095 --> 12:09.761
deciding on
     one Photoshopped image

12:09.763 --> 12:11.896
whether or not to engage
     in immediate foreplay?

12:11.898 --> 12:14.065
I'm busy.
     You're weird. Goodbye.

12:16.570 --> 12:18.770
(register beeping)

12:21.274 --> 12:24.175
¶ ¶

12:24.177 --> 12:26.077
Can...

12:26.079 --> 12:29.514
Um... do you need any...

12:35.422 --> 12:37.689
-(drawer closes)
       -(register beeps)

12:37.691 --> 12:39.023
Good evening.

12:39.025 --> 12:40.759
Good eve... (gasps)

12:42.362 --> 12:44.262
Can I help you?

12:44.264 --> 12:45.930
I think so.

12:47.901 --> 12:49.567
Go on, then.

12:49.569 --> 12:52.570
What is it
     you were looking for?

12:52.572 --> 12:54.105
Um...

12:55.876 --> 12:57.575
This.

12:57.577 --> 12:59.944
That is very nice.

12:59.946 --> 13:02.380
It's Mr. Claus, I believe.

13:02.382 --> 13:03.581
Yes.

13:03.583 --> 13:05.216
Upon his vehicle.

13:05.218 --> 13:08.086
-Yes.
   -Do you have something...

13:08.088 --> 13:09.621
dissimilar?

13:09.623 --> 13:11.089
