         -Join a club.

36:55.180 --> 36:57.214
Hmm? Talk to other people.

36:57.216 --> 36:58.748
Enjoy time with your friends.

36:58.750 --> 37:01.351
-All my friends were murdered.
          -Okay, fine.

37:01.353 --> 37:02.986
Thank you, Doctor. Thank you
     so much for your time.

37:02.988 --> 37:04.521
-But it's-it's true.
    -Let's go, Mum. Come on.

37:04.523 --> 37:05.722
-They took them.
-Mum, come on. Come on. I know.

37:05.724 --> 37:07.157
-Thank you. Um... -Come on,
    Mama, out we get. Sorry.

37:07.159 --> 37:08.592
-Sorry. Let's go. -Kate, we'll
  see you in a... in a month.

37:08.594 --> 37:09.826
-(speaking Serbo-Croatian)
      -See you next year.

37:09.828 --> 37:11.394
-There you go. All right.
     -I am coming. I come.

37:11.396 --> 37:12.729
-Get-get out the-- Right.
          -I'm coming.

37:12.731 --> 37:14.731
-Thank you. -(door closes)
     -(sighs) Bloody hell.

37:14.733 --> 37:16.766
¶ ¶

37:28.947 --> 37:30.247
(bell jingles)

37:30.249 --> 37:31.881
Can I help?

37:31.883 --> 37:33.250
No.

37:33.252 --> 37:35.285
I'm having a self-pity party.

37:35.287 --> 37:36.620
Ooh.

37:36.622 --> 37:38.688
Am I invited?

37:38.690 --> 37:40.690
Well, only if you promise
          to judge me.

37:40.692 --> 37:43.393
Oh, you definitely don't need
      any help doing that.

37:43.395 --> 37:45.395
Or maybe you do.

37:45.397 --> 37:47.364
I'm very good at tidying up.

37:47.366 --> 37:48.932
(clears throat)

37:50.902 --> 37:52.469
Yes.

38:10.155 --> 38:11.621
-These expensive?
          -(rattling)

38:11.623 --> 38:13.423
(Kate stammers)

38:13.425 --> 38:16.293
Idiot. Follow me.

38:17.262 --> 38:18.662
Ah.

38:18.664 --> 38:20.430
(singsongy):
            Tra-la.

38:20.432 --> 38:23.900
All right, Mr. Muscle, you can
  get to refreshing that tree.

38:23.902 --> 38:25.402
-This one?
             -Yeah.

38:28.840 --> 38:31.207
Going home
     always makes me crazy.

38:32.244 --> 38:33.276
How was it?

38:33.278 --> 38:34.844
Hell. Mum sung me to sleep.

38:34.846 --> 38:36.913
You're the only person

38:36.915 --> 38:39.316
who can make being sung to
sleep sound like waterboarding.

38:39.318 --> 38:42.252
Well, it's not that dissimilar.

38:42.254 --> 38:43.853
(laughing):
     These, um, folk songs

38:43.855 --> 38:45.922
make you want
     to string yourself up.

38:45.924 --> 38:47.991
Is that where you get
       your singing from?

38:47.993 --> 38:50.794
Yeah, she was a singer
   back in, um, the homeland.

38:50.796 --> 38:52.295
Where was that?

38:52.297 --> 38:54.831
Former Yugoslavia.
       We had to escape.

38:54.833 --> 38:57.033
-'Cause of the war?
           -Exactly.

38:57.035 --> 38:59.703
Mm. Must have been hard.

38:59.705 --> 39:01.938
Yeah. Dad was a lawyer.

39:01.940 --> 39:05.208
Um, and now he stays away
  from home as much as he can

39:05.210 --> 39:07.043
because he'd rather be dead.
           (chuckles)

39:07.045 --> 39:08.478
Except he's a minicab driver,

39:08.480 --> 39:11.181
which is sort of
        the same thing.

39:11.183 --> 39:13.216
Can he not practice here?

39:13.218 --> 39:14.351
No, he couldn't afford
          to retrain,

39:14.353 --> 39:16.486
so he's out all the time.

39:16.488 --> 39:18.288
Also to avoid my mother,

39:18.290 --> 39:22.625
who's given to depression
 in much the same way as, um...

39:22.627 --> 39:24.661
What?
   You're looking at me like

39:24.663 --> 39:26.696
some sort of science experiment
       that's gone wrong.

39:26.698 --> 39:27.897
Sorry.

39:27.899 --> 39:30.400
-No, I'm interested.
             -Huh.

39:30.402 --> 39:32.168
I mean, your mother--
     when was the last time

39:32.170 --> 39:33.336
you saw her
      not being depressed?

39:33.338 --> 39:35.071
(chuckles)

39:35.073 --> 39:37.907
Ooh, I think
     when I got really ill.

39:37.909 --> 39:39.576
And she was happy about that?

39:39.578 --> 39:43.480
No, but she was happy
      about the attention.

39:43.482 --> 39:45.382
I mean,
   I got a lot of attention,

39:45.384 --> 39:47.484
but I was unconscious.

39:47.486 --> 39:49.052
She got more.

39:49.054 --> 39:53.056
Just the doctors,
the nurses, the hospital staff.

39:53.058 --> 39:54.891
Drama. God, she loved it.

39:54.893 --> 39:56.993
She sort of flowered
       under it like a...

39:56.995 --> 39:58.995
like a late blossoming
         or something.

39:58.997 --> 40:02.232
Anyway, when I got better,
       it all went away,

40:02.234 --> 40:04.501
and she's just never
      been the same since.

40:04.503 --> 40:06.569
Well, maybe she enjoyed
      being needed again.

40:06.571 --> 40:08.938
Oh, trust you to come up
 with something understanding.

40:10.175 --> 40:11.875
-That is truly horrific.
        -(Kate chuckles)

40:11.877 --> 40:13.710
I mean, who buys this stuff?

40:13.712 --> 40:16.880
Santa. She's Chinese,
      so she's, you know,

40:16.882 --> 40:20.250
got access to some
     really freaky outlets.

40:20.252 --> 40:23.286
She just loves Christmas
    more than anything else.

40:23.288 --> 40:26.523
-More than taste or sanity.
         -Yes, exactly.

40:26.525 --> 40:29.592
And that isn't even
  the nastiest thing we sell.

40:29.594 --> 40:30.727
Inconceivable.

40:30.729 --> 40:32.195
Hang on.

40:34.399 --> 40:37.567
-¶ Dun, dun, dun! ¶
              -Oh!

40:37.569 --> 40:39.302
-Check it out.
          -What is it?

40:39.304 --> 40:41.738
-Is that donkey actually
  smiling at me? -Yeah. Yeah.

40:41.740 --> 40:43.306
And that baby
    has a full set of teeth.

40:43.308 --> 40:45.942
-Oof. -I sold four of these
   last week. I'm that good.

40:45.944 --> 40:47.544
(techno version
  of "Last Christmas" playing)

40:47.546 --> 40:49.579
Oh, it's a...
   oh, it's a techno manger.

40:49.581 --> 40:51.080
-Yeah.
     -Oh, yeah, yeah. Cool.

40:51.082 --> 40:52.816
-It's a disco nativity scene.
          -(laughing)

40:52.818 --> 40:54.784
Is that really
   a good nutritional choice?

40:54.786 --> 40:56.286
Oh, God, don't you start.

40:56.288 --> 40:58.221
Where are you?

40:58.223 --> 40:59.489
Look up.

41:01.393 --> 41:03.126
Yeah.

41:03.128 --> 41:05.161
Yeah, after you...
   what you've been through,

41:05.163 --> 41:07.931
I mean, shouldn't you be eating
  quinoa or kale or something?

41:07.933 --> 41:10.834
Yeah, but this
     admittedly rank burger

41:10.836 --> 41:12.902
is all part of my grand plan

41:12.904 --> 41:15.638
to become a famous singer
   and die like Kurt Cobain,

41:15.640 --> 41:18.341
Amy Winehouse and all the rest
       at the age of 27.

41:19.511 --> 41:21.578
-How old are you?
              -45.

41:21.580 --> 41:23.112
Oh. Good to have dreams.

41:23.114 --> 41:24.280
Not really. I'm 26.

41:24.282 --> 41:25.815
Oh, thank God.
      You still have time.

41:25.817 --> 41:27.150
(chuckles)

41:27.152 --> 41:29.452
-Come on. Get rid of that.
        -Where...? Wait.

41:29.454 --> 41:31.488
Let's go.
  I've got a surprise for you.

41:33.992 --> 41:37.494
-Ugh, really? (laughs)
          -Mm, yummy!

41:38.930 --> 41:40.363
There's something wrong
       with me, you know.

41:40.365 --> 41:41.931
-I'm too trusting.
         -(Tom scoffs)

41:41.933 --> 41:44.133
Down a dark alley again
   with a complete stranger.

41:44.135 --> 41:45.335
I don't even...
       I mean, seriously,

41:45.337 --> 41:48.071
-where are you... (chuckles)
    -Pop yourself over here.

41:49.841 --> 41:51.441
-All right, then.
         -Need a hand?

41:51.443 --> 41:53.009
No.

41:53.011 --> 41:54.677
-(grunting): Oh, Christ.
              -Oh.

41:54.679 --> 41:57.447
-(groans) Oh, my God.
   -Oh! That looked painful.

41:57.449 --> 41:59.516
-Yeah. I'm fine. I'm fine!
    -Ah, you... you're fine.

41:59.518 --> 42:01.050
That was like poetry in motion.

42:01.052 --> 42:02.318
-Piss off.
           -Come on.

42:02.320 --> 42:05.021
Sure. Never wanted kids anyway.
            (grunts)

42:05.023 --> 42:06.890
(Kate groaning)

42:06.892 --> 42:08.391
Okay.

42:08.393 --> 42:09.893
Now I am intrigued.

42:09.895 --> 42:11.794
-How are you gonna dispose
      of my body? -Shh...

42:11.796 --> 42:14.631
-Shh!
       -I... am shh-ing.

42:16.201 --> 42:17.867
(imitating Sean Connery):
           Stay back.

42:17.869 --> 42:20.203
Are you seriously doing
    a James Bond impression?

42:20.205 --> 42:22.639
Now is not the time
      for unpleasantness.

42:22.641 --> 42:25.909
Now is the time... for romance!

42:25.911 --> 42:28.378
("Praying for Time"
   by George Michael playing)

42:34.486 --> 42:36.753
You like?

42:36.755 --> 42:38.588
I like, yeah.

42:38.590 --> 42:40.056
Let's go.

42:42.060 --> 42:46.162
¶ These are the days
       of the open hand ¶

42:46.164 --> 42:49.599
¶ They will not be the last ¶

42:49.601 --> 42:51.935
¶ Look around now ¶

42:51.937 --> 42:56.606
¶ These are the days of
 the beggars and the choosers ¶

42:56.608 --> 43:00.677
¶ This is the year
      of the hungry man ¶

43:00.679 --> 43:04.380
¶ Whose place is in the past ¶

43:04.382 --> 43:08.184
¶ Hand in hand with ignorance ¶

43:08.186 --> 43:12.889
¶ And legitimate excuses ¶

43:12.891 --> 43:16.125
¶ The rich declare
       themselves poor ¶

43:16.127 --> 43:19.529
¶ And most of us are not sure ¶

43:19.531 --> 43:21.297
¶ If we have too much ¶

43:21.299 --> 43:23.700
¶ But we'll take our chances ¶

43:23.702 --> 43:26.903
¶ 'Cause God's stopped
        keeping score ¶

43:26.905 --> 43:30.773
¶ I guess somewhere
        along the way ¶

43:30.775 --> 43:35.445
¶ He must have let us
       all out to play ¶

43:35.447 --> 43:39.582
¶ Turned his back,
    and all God's children ¶

43:39.584 --> 43:42.452
¶ Crept out the back door ¶

43:43.955 --> 43:47.256
¶ Well, maybe
       we should all be ¶

43:47.258 --> 43:49.425
¶ Praying for time... ¶

43:49.427 --> 43:51.561
-Oi!
     -Oh, sorry! -Oh, crap.

43:51.563 --> 43:53.763
-You can't be in here!
     -Yeah, no. -Sorry, no.

43:53.765 --> 43:55.231
-We're-we're leaving.
  -Absolutely, we're leaving.

43:55.233 --> 43:56.299
-Sorry... (screams)
             -Whoa!

43:56.301 --> 43:57.767
-(Kate squeals)
           -TOM: Oh!

43:57.769 --> 43:59.969
(both laugh, whooping)

43:59.971 --> 44:01.771
-(groans) Ow!
        -(Tom chuckling)

44:01.773 --> 44:03.106
KATE:
     I'm coming. I'm com...

44:03.108 --> 44:05.575
(both chuckle and sigh)

44:05.577 --> 44:09.078
I would, uh... I'd call that
       a successful date.

44:09.080 --> 44:12.615
Fun, free, illegal, romantic.

44:12.617 --> 44:14.450
-And practical, too.
    Don't forget. -(laughs)

44:14.452 --> 44:15.652
Why practical?

44:15.654 --> 44:16.786
Your audition.

44:16.788 --> 44:18.521
-Remember?
             -Yes.

44:18.523 --> 44:21.591
I'd like to think that I played
a part in your rise to stardom.

44:21.593 --> 44:23.660
-(laughs) -Remember me
    when you're at the top.

44:23.662 --> 44:26.596
No chance. Tom who?

44:26.598 --> 44:28.398
Actually, Tom who?

44:29.534 --> 44:31.034
Webster.

44:31.036 --> 44:32.535
Huh.

44:32.537 --> 44:34.404
You look like a Webster.

44:36.441 --> 44:38.274
Now what?

44:39.310 --> 44:41.344
Now I've got to go to work.

44:43.148 --> 44:44.981
Um...

44:44.983 --> 44:46.683
You knew.

44:46.685 --> 44:49.619
-I work nights.
             -Yes.

44:49.621 --> 44:51.654
I knew.

44:51.656 --> 44:54.524
It's night. Cool. Okay.

44:54.526 --> 44:55.858
How you gonna get home?

44:55.860 --> 44:58.628
-Oh, the bus.
         -(Tom grunts)

44:58.630 --> 45:00.997
You gonna be okay?

45:00.999 --> 45:03.833
As okay as I'll ever be
          on the bus.

45:03.835 --> 45:05.034
Okay, then.

45:05.036 --> 45:06.803
I'll come find you at the shop.

45:06.805 --> 45:09.505
(chuckling): I'm not sure
    if I've still got a job.

45:09.507 --> 45:11.340
Santa kind of hates me.

45:11.342 --> 45:13.643
Maybe you should do
   something nice for Santa.

45:13.645 --> 45:15.244
¶ ¶

45:15.246 --> 45:16.879
Good luck.

45:20.919 --> 45:22.919
Look up.

45:25.356 --> 45:27.657
-(chuckles softly)
         -(horn honks)

45:27.659 --> 45:29.025
-(brakes squealing)
        -(horn honking)

45:29.027 --> 45:30.560
Christ.

45:32.163 --> 45:33.563
So, this is our selection

45:33.565 --> 45:35.331
-of nutcrackers.
    -Working hard over here.

45:35.333 --> 45:36.866
-Mm-hmm.
              -Mm.

45:36.868 --> 45:38.401
You know, from the ballet?

45:38.403 --> 45:39.669
-Tchaikovsky?
          -WOMAN: Ah.

45:39.671 --> 45:41.003
MAN:
  Which kind of music is this?

45:41.005 --> 45:42.739
-I want something to be...
   -WOMAN: Listen. Be quiet.

45:42.741 --> 45:43.940
SANTA:
    This is Christmas music.

45:43.942 --> 45:45.808
You must enjoy it.

45:52.684 --> 45:54.083
SANTA:
   This is a big nutcracker.

45:54.085 --> 45:56.085
MAN:
 Can my nuts fit inside there?

45:56.087 --> 45:57.787
SANTA: Uh, depends on
     how big are your nuts.

45:57.789 --> 45:59.889
WOMAN: But it's too big.
  We can't take that with us.

45:59.891 --> 46:02.859
Santa, um, I think
  I can take over from there.

46:02.861 --> 46:05.561
Because, um, there's also
   someone here, a gentleman,

46:05.563 --> 46:07.897
who requires
   your specific assistance.

46:07.899 --> 46:09.265
SANTA:
   Yes, you can have a look.

46:09.267 --> 46:10.433
Think about it.

46:10.435 --> 46:11.734
KATE:
     I'm gonna show you to

46:11.736 --> 46:13.236
the even bigger nutcrackers
       around the corner.

46:13.238 --> 46:14.937
MAN:
      There's bigger nuts?

46:14.939 --> 46:17.774
-KATE: For your big nuts.
     Here we are. -MAN: Oh.

46:19.144 --> 46:21.844
Have you come back
        for the gibbon?

46:23.081 --> 46:26.149
Of all the things in my life,

46:26.151 --> 46:30.286
this is my best thing.

46:30.288 --> 46:31.888
What is?

46:31.890 --> 46:33.790
Christmas.

46:35.593 --> 46:36.993
Really?

46:36.995 --> 46:38.961
This is why I love
        to come in here.

46:38.963 --> 46:40.663
I also love it.

46:40.665 --> 46:43.366
That is why I have this shop.

46:44.569 --> 46:46.169
Oh, wow.

46:46.171 --> 46:48.571
(chuckles softly)

46:48.573 --> 46:52.809
¶ Have a holly jolly
          Christmas ¶

46:52.811 --> 46:56.179
¶ And in case you didn't hear ¶

46:56.181 --> 46:57.680
¶ Oh, by golly ¶

46:57.682 --> 47:02.418
¶ Have a holly jolly Christmas
          this year. ¶

47:02.420 --> 47:04.086
(applause)

47:04.088 --> 47:06.189
Kate, that was lovely.
           Thank you.

47:06.191 --> 47:08.424
Wonderful.
  I can smell the commitment.

47:08.426 --> 47:10.293
Do you know we have people
         turn up here,

47:10.295 --> 47:11.761
never been
     on an ice rink before?

47:11.763 --> 47:13.996
(laughing):
    I just couldn't imagine.

47:13.998 --> 47:16.599
Do you know we had a woman
     turn up in a crop top?

47:16.601 --> 47:18.267
-In a crop top to audition.
       -Yeah, I remember.

47:18.269 --> 47:19.468
Do you remember her flip-flops?

47:19.470 --> 47:21.204
-Remember those? -Of course
    I remember. -I remember.

47:21.206 --> 47:22.672
CASTING DIRECTOR:
 Thank you. We'll be in touch.

47:22.674 --> 47:23.873
-DIRECTOR: Thank you so much.
          -Thank you.

47:23.875 --> 47:25.308
Thank you. Thank you.

47:25.310 --> 47:27.343
I think she'd be good
for the horse. Don't you think?

47:27.345 --> 47:28.711
-DIRECTOR: No, we can...
         -KATE: Oh, no!

47:30.648 --> 47:33.049
-DIRECTOR: Are you all right?
      -I, uh... I did that

47:33.051 --> 47:36.152
just in case you thought
       I was too perfect.

47:36.154 --> 47:37.720
KATE:
             Okay.

47:38.790 --> 47:39.956
Okay.

47:39.958 --> 47:41.657
DIRECTOR: Thank goodness
   for a heavy woolen tight.

47:41.659 --> 47:43.626
KATE:
             Idiot.

47:43.628 --> 47:44.894
Skaters fall. It's fine.

47:44.896 --> 47:46.395
MAN:
      ...at the same time.

47:46.397 --> 47:48.130
Also, nobody's clapping.
    (continues indistinctly)

47:48.132 --> 47:49.932
-(scattered applause)
     -(indistinct chatter)

47:55.840 --> 47:57.907
-(applause)
       -(crowd murmuring)

48:01.512 --> 48:04.046
So, it went well,
        and I am happy.

48:04.048 --> 48:05.848
Good.

48:05.850 --> 48:07.583
All set for your date?

48:07.585 --> 48:08.684
Good Lord.

48:08.686 --> 48:09.986
(clears throat)

48:11.756 --> 48:12.755
Okay.

48:12.757 --> 48:14.824
-Right, um...
             -What?

48:14.826 --> 48:16.826
We're just gonna need
       to dial this down.

48:16.828 --> 48:18.194
I'm making an effort.

48:18.196 --> 48:19.595
He's gonna think he's wandered

48:19.597 --> 48:21.764
into the llama enclosure.
             Close.

48:21.766 --> 48:22.999
(sighs)

48:23.001 --> 48:24.333
Ow.

48:24.335 --> 48:25.902
KATE:
            Mm-hmm.

48:25.904 --> 48:27.603
-Ow.
           -Oh, yeah.

48:27.605 --> 48:28.871
Serves you right.

48:28.873 --> 48:30.740
So I defer to the Swiper queen.

48:30.742 --> 48:32.642
-Blot.
            -Mm, mm.

48:34.445 --> 48:36.345
There we are.

48:36.347 --> 48:39.448
So, where is See-Through
          taking you?

48:39.450 --> 48:41.684
-I have no idea.
       -What's his name?

48:41.686 --> 48:43.019
I can't pronounce it.

48:43.021 --> 48:45.021
Lots of glottal stops.

48:45.023 --> 48:47.023
"Yogh..." (hawking)

48:47.025 --> 48:48.524
Oh, when I try to say it,

48:48.526 --> 48:50.626
I sound like a cat
        with a fur ball.

48:50.628 --> 48:53.062
So I've decided
       to call him "Boy."

48:53.064 --> 48:55.731
Mm. Well, at least your name's
      easier to pronounce.

48:55.733 --> 48:57.667
What? Huang Qing Shin?

48:59.203 --> 49:01.103
You're not really called Santa?

49:01.105 --> 49:02.738
Of course not, idiot.

49:02.740 --> 49:05.074
-I chose it for the shop.
            -Really?

49:05.076 --> 49:07.209
Yeah, when I worked
        at the pet shop,

49:07.211 --> 49:08.577
I called myself Kitty.

49:08.579 --> 49:09.912
-No.
            -Mm-hmm.

49:09.914 --> 49:14.083
And at the health food shop,
          I was Miso.

49:14.085 --> 49:16.452
-No, no.
       -Mm-hmm. Yes, yes.

49:16.454 --> 49:18.888
Guess what it was in the bakery
      on the Edgware Road.

49:18.890 --> 49:20.256
Uh, Crumpet?

49:20.258 --> 49:22.258
-Sausage Roll?
            -Muffin.

49:22.260 --> 49:23.926
-(laughs): Muffin?
       -"Muff" for short.

49:23.928 --> 49:25.227
Excellent.

49:25.229 --> 49:27.730
More important is:
         how do I look?

49:28.800 --> 49:30.232
Really hot.

49:30.234 --> 49:31.634
(giggles)

49:31.636 --> 49:34.170
Did you just giggle
          like a girl?

49:34.172 --> 49:35.471
I am a girl.

49:35.473 --> 49:36.939
-Not really.
